---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1%unit}; dry thoroughly with #paper towels{}. (TIP: Be sure to remove as much moisture as possible—this will help reduce the popping that can happen as chickpeas roast!) Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1%unit} into ½-inch-thick wedges.

Toss chickpeas and onion on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle}, half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest later), @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}.

Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until chickpeas are crispy and onion is tender and lightly charred, ~{18-20%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @basmati rice{1/2%cup}, @chicken stock concentrate{1%unit}, and 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings); season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with paper towels and cut into bite-size pieces if needed. Season all over with half the @sumac{1%teaspoon} (all for 4 servings), remaining garlic powder, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken in a single layer; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate{}.

Strip @parsley{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; mince leaves. Zest and quarter @lemon{1%unit}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @hummus{4%tablespoon}, 2 tsp water (4 tsp for 4 servings), a pinch of parsley, a pinch of lemon zest, a squeeze of lemon juice (big squeeze for 4), and a drizzle of olive oil (large drizzle for 4).

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; taste and season with salt and pepper. Stir in chicken.

Divide chicken-rice mixture between #bowls{} and top with roasted chickpeas and onion. Drizzle with hummus sauce and garnish with remaining parsley. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.